  "prompt": "What is a list of formula sheets for each subject for the GATE in mechanical to cope with last minute preparation?",
  "response": "Here's a comprehensive list of formula sheets for GATE Mechanical Engineering:\n\n1. Strength of Materials\n- Stress and strain formulas\n- Beam deflection equations\n- Failure theories\n- Torsion formulas\n- Stress concentration factors\n\n2. Thermodynamics\n- Laws of thermodynamics\n- Heat transfer equations\n- Efficiency calculations\n- Carnot cycle formulas\n- Entropy and enthalpy calculations\n\n3. Machine Design\n- Gear design formulas\n- Bearing load capacity\n- Shaft design equations\n- Stress concentration factors\n- Failure theories\n\n4. Heat Transfer\n- Conduction formulas\n- Convection heat transfer coefficients\n- Radiation heat transfer equations\n- Heat exchanger effectiveness\n- Temperature difference calculations\n\n5. Fluid Mechanics\n- Reynolds number\n- Drag coefficient equations\n- Bernoulli's equation\n- Flow rate calculations\n- Pressure drop formulas\n\n6. Theory of Machines\n- Velocity and acceleration analysis\n- Dynamic force calculations\n- Cam and follower design\n- Gear kinematics\n- Balancing of rotating masses\n\n7. Manufacturing\n- Machining parameters\n- Cutting speed formulas\n- Surface roughness equations\n- Metal removal rate\n- Tolerance and fits\n\n8. Engineering Mathematics\n- Differential equations\n- Integration techniques\n- Probability and statistics\n- Laplace transforms\n- Trigonometric formulas\n\n9. IC Engines\n- Performance parameters\n- Fuel consumption calculations\n- Combustion efficiency\n- Engine cycles\n- Emission calculations\n\n10. Refrigeration and Air Conditioning\n- COP calculations\n- Psychrometric chart formulas\n- Load estimation\n- Compressor efficiency\n- Cooling capacity equations\n\nTips for Last-Minute Preparation:\n- Create compact formula sheets\n- Practice solving problems quickly\n- Focus on understanding applications\n- Memorize key equations\n- Review derivations\n\nRecommended Resources:\n- GATE previous year question papers\n- Standard reference books\n- Online formula compilations\n- Mock test series\n- Subject-specific formula handbooks\n\nSuggested Study Approach:\n1. Understand fundamental concepts\n2. Memorize core formulas\n3. Practice problem-solving\n4. Time management\n5. Regular revision\n\nImportant Sections to Prioritize:\n- Strength of Materials\n- Thermodynamics\n- Heat Transfer\n- Machine Design\n- Fluid Mechanics\n\nFinal Preparation Strategy:\n- Solve multiple mock tests\n- Review formula sheets daily\n- Practice time-bound problem-solving\n- Stay calm and confident\n- Get adequate rest before exam\n\nCommon Mistake Areas:\n- Unit conversions\n- Dimensional analysis\n- Complex equation applications\n- Multi-step problem-solving\n\nAdditional Recommendations:\n- Create digital and physical formula sheets\n- Use color-coding for better retention\n- Practice mental calculations\n- Focus on understanding underlying principles\n\nWarning:\n- Don't solely rely on formula memorization\n- Conceptual understanding is crucial\n- Practice applying formulas in various contexts\n\nExpected Formula Sheet Length:\n- 4-6 pages maximum\n- Concise and precise content\n- Clear, legible writing\n- Include key constants and conversion factors\n\nRecommended Formula Organization:\n- Group by subject\n- Use tables and diagrams\n- Highlight critical equations\n- Include units and dimensions\n\nBy following these guidelines and creating comprehensive formula sheets, you can enhance your GATE Mechanical Engineering preparation and improve your problem-solving efficiency.",
